kernel_variant.question:
Let $ABCD$ be a convex bicentric quadrilateral; that is, $ABCD$ is simultaneously tangential (possesses an incircle of radius $r$) and cyclic.  
Denote
\[
AB=a,\qquad BC=b,\qquad CD=c,\qquad DA=d,\qquad 
p=\frac{a+b+c+d}{2}\quad\text{(semiperimeter)} .
\]

Prove the inequality
\[
\boxed{\;
\frac{1}{(p-a)^{2}}+\frac{1}{(p-b)^{2}}
+\frac{1}{(p-c)^{2}}+\frac{1}{(p-d)^{2}}
\;\ge\;
\frac{1}{r^{2}}
\;}
\tag{\*}
\]
and show that equality is attained if and only if $ABCD$ is a square.

